1
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:18,000
Doctor Who (1963) 04x09  The Evil of the Daleks (Episode 4)
《神秘博士》老版第四季第九集 《Daleks 的邪恶》 (第四部分)

2
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:23,000
【翻译】巴蛮子sz

3
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:26,000
【时间轴】巴蛮子sz

4
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:29,000
【校对】巴蛮子sz

5
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:32,000
<i>基于 opentitles.org 英文字幕翻译</i>

6
00:00:32,050 --> 00:00:35,656
Hello? Who are you?
你好？你是谁？

7
00:00:35,980 --> 00:00:38,306
<i>(Sincro: wyxchari)</i>

8
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:46,306
<i>(Kemel runs towards Jamie gripping him in a bear hug.)</i>
<i>（Kemel 朝 Jamie 跑过来，一个熊抱扑住了他）</i>

9
00:00:51,100 --> 00:00:55,306
<i>(He manages to break free.)</i>
Jamie 用力挣脱了

10
00:01:04,100 --> 00:01:09,706
<i>(Kemel knocks Jamie to the floor.)</i>
Kemel 又把 Jamie 撞到在地上

11
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:23,806
<i>(Lashing out with his leg, Jamie sends Kemel crashing into  a suit of armour.)</i>
Jamie 伸出腿，把 Kemel 绊倒，Kemel 摔倒在一副盔甲中

12
00:01:35,100 --> 00:01:39,306
<i>(Jamie runs through an open door and slams it shut.)</i>
Jaime 跑过一道门，砰地一下关上

13
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:52,306
<i>(Kemel recovers and sets off after Jamie.)</i>
Kemel 爬起身来，又来追 Jaime

14
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:15,906
<i>(Jame takes a sword from the wall.)</i>
Jamie 从墙上抄起一把剑

15
00:02:30,500 --> 00:02:35,306
<i>(Jamie hears Kemel approaching.)</i>
他听见 Kemel 走近了

16
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:40,306
<i>(Kemel runs towards Jamie, He jumps out of the way.)</i>
Kemel 朝 Jamie 跑过来，Jamie 一跳躲开了

17
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:45,906
<i>(Kemel goes flying out of a window, catching the guttering to save himself.)</i>
Kemel 从窗户飞了出去，急伸手抓住了屋檐

18
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:55,306
<i>(Jamie climbs onto the roof.)</i>
Jaime 爬到了屋顶上

19
00:03:03,500 --> 00:03:08,306
<i>(Kemel is unable to pull himself up.)</i>
Kemel 没法把自己的身子拉上来

20
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:23,806
<i>(Jamie helps Kemel to climb back onto the roof.)</i>
Jaime 拉 Kemel，帮他爬回了屋顶

21
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:39,906
<i>(A Dalek goes by, unnoticed, on the floor below.)</i>
他们没注意到，一个 Dalek 从下面走过

22
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:58,806
<i>(The Dalek places the handkerchief in an empty room.)</i>
这个 Dalek 把手绢放入了一个空房间

23
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:08,306
<i>(Kemel lowers Jamie to the first floor.)</i>
Kemel 吊着 Jamie，把他放到了地板上

24
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:14,306
<i>(Jamie spots the handkerchief.)</i>
Jamie 看到了手绢

25
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:25,606
<i>(Kemel pulls Jamie clear as a blade comes crashing down.)</i>

26
00:04:37,500 --> 00:04:41,806
<i>(Jamie and Kemel exchange glances, then Kemel helps the dazed Jamie from the room.)</i>

27
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:02,806
<i>(They go up a flight of stairs.)</i>

28
00:05:16,052 --> 00:05:19,582
DOCTOR: It took courage to fight Maxtible's Turkish wrestler.
跟 Maxtible 的土耳其斗士搏斗, 是很需要勇气的

29
00:05:20,459 --> 00:05:25,357
DALEK: The Daleks are afraid of nothing and no one.
Daleks 不怕任何东西, 也不怕任何人

30
00:05:25,908 --> 00:05:28,402
DOCTOR: But Jamie saved the Turk's life.
但 Jamie 又救了那个土耳其人的命

31
00:05:28,729 --> 00:05:30,508
DALEK: Human weakness.
人类的弱点

32
00:05:30,802 --> 00:05:40,582
DOCTOR: If he hadn't, he would have died in that room of yours.
If you want the Human Factor, a part of it must include mercy.
如果他没有救, 他就会死在你们的房间里了。如果你想要人类特质, “仁慈”肯定是其中一项

33
00:05:46,605 --> 00:05:49,209
WATERFIELD: What... what is he doing here?
他。。。他在这里做什么？

34
00:05:49,897 --> 00:05:56,177
MAXTIBLE: A common thief, come to see what he could steal.
No mystery here.
一个普通小贼, 进来看看有什么可偷的, 估计就是这样

35
00:06:00,283 --> 00:06:03,287
DALEK: The intruder was destroyed.
闯入者已经被毁灭

36
00:06:04,116 --> 00:06:08,047
WATERFIELD: Well, what... what are we to do? Where is the Doctor?
He must be told.
那。。。我们该怎么办？博士哪儿去了？肯定得告诉他啊

37
00:06:08,297 --> 00:06:08,844
DALEK: No.
不用

38
00:06:09,067 --> 00:06:09,768
WATERFIELD: Why not?
为什么不用？

39
00:06:10,014 --> 00:06:10,975
DALEK: Obey me!
服从我!

40
00:06:11,703 --> 00:06:16,116
MAXTIBLE: Waterfield, I... I beg of you, do not antagonize the, um... 
Waterfield, 我求你了, 不要激怒这些。。。唔

41
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:17,117
MAXTIBLE: ...our friends.
。。。朋友

42
00:06:17,329 --> 00:06:22,470
WATERFIELD: Oh, why do you consistently avoid reality, Maxtible?
Another man has died. Can't you grasp that fact?
噢, 你为什么一直都要逃避现实呢, Maxtible？又一个人死了, 你还没看明白吗？

43
00:06:22,715 --> 00:06:27,233
DALEK: You will hide the remains of the dead human intruder.
你要把这位闯入者的尸体藏起来

44
00:06:27,827 --> 00:06:28,475
WATERFIELD: No!
不!

45
00:06:28,761 --> 00:06:29,939
DELKS: That is an order!
这是一项命令！

46
00:06:30,155 --> 00:06:32,960
MAXTIBLE: We must do as they say, Waterfield. We... we cannot anger them.
我们必须按他们说的做, Waterfield. 我们。。。我们不能激怒他们

47
00:06:33,202 --> 00:06:36,614
MAXTIBLE: Here. Wrap the body in this.
这里, 把尸体卷到这里面来

48
00:06:37,070 --> 00:06:38,568
WATERFIELD: No.
不

49
00:06:38,870 --> 00:06:42,568
<i>(Maxtible takes a dust sheet from beneath the bench.)</i>
<i>（Maxtible 从工作台下拿出一个防尘板）</i>
MAXTIBLE: We must! Have you lost your mind?
我们得干！你疯了吗？

50
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:44,262
MAXTIBLE: Don't you want to see your daughter again?
不想再见到你女儿了？

51
00:06:46,085 --> 00:06:51,772
WATERFIELD: Th... there's no end to this. The hands of the Devil.
这。。。这有没有个尽头, 魔鬼的手

52
00:06:52,135 --> 00:06:55,823
DALEK: Dispose of the body. Obey!
处理掉尸体。服从！

53
00:06:56,135 --> 00:06:58,623
<i>(The Dalek enters the cabinet.)</i>

54
00:06:58,803 --> 00:07:06,668
MAXTIBLE：Waterfield, what is the matter with you?
We are not to blame for everything that has happened.
Waterfield, 你到底是怎么了？发生了这一切, 并不是我们的错啊

55
00:07:06,803 --> 00:07:11,668
MAXTIBLE: No English judge or jury would find it in their hearts
to convict us of one solitary thing.
这里的任何一件事, 没有那个英国法官或者陪审团在他们的心里会认为该定我们的罪

56
00:07:13,072 --> 00:07:14,392
WATERFIELD: It will never come to that.
不会到那一步的

57
00:07:15,102 --> 00:07:17,760
MAXTIBLE: And what may that remark mean?
这句话是什么意思？

58
00:07:17,969 --> 00:07:26,230
WATERFIELD: I have one purpose only: to see my daughter
out of the hands of those foul monsters.
我就一个目的：看到我的女儿逃出这些怪物的魔爪

59
00:07:26,469 --> 00:07:31,230
WATERFIELD: When that is achieved, I shall confess my part
in all that has happened.
一旦这个目的达到了, 我会坦白我在所有这一切中所扮演的角色

60
00:07:34,069 --> 00:07:39,230
<i>(Waterfield drags the body away.)</i>

61
00:07:42,469 --> 00:07:47,230
<i>(Maxtible goes to a drawer, takes out a pistol and puts it into his coat.)</i>

62
00:07:50,203 --> 00:07:53,009
WATERFIELD: Y... You must help me.
你。。。你必须帮我

63
00:07:53,358 --> 00:07:55,760
MAXTIBLE: I am at your heels, my dear sir.
我马上就来, 我亲爱的朋友

64
00:08:00,076 --> 00:08:05,451
JAMIE: That's better, thank you.
Aye, you're an odd one. I'll say that.
好多了, 谢谢你。啊, 你是个奇怪的家伙, 我得说。

65
00:08:05,676 --> 00:08:09,451
JAMIE: Aye, well, I... I suppose we're both a a bit touched, eh?
啊, 我猜咱们俩都有点感动了, 对不？

66
00:08:10,076 --> 00:08:15,151
JAMIE: Knocking each other about the place and saving one another's lives.
在这里打得死去活来, 然后又相互救了对方的命

67
00:08:18,144 --> 00:08:19,765
JAMIE: You don't say much, do you?
你很少说话, 是吧

68
00:08:22,633 --> 00:08:24,503
JAMIE: Oh, I see. You can't talk?
哦, 我明白了, 你不能说话？

69
00:08:24,633 --> 00:08:28,003
JAMIE: Aye. Well, you're a sight better than a number of people I know who can.
啊, 这样啊, 你比我认识的很多会说话的人还好

70
00:08:28,233 --> 00:08:30,703
JAMIE: I wonder what your name is?
你叫什么名字？

71
00:08:33,233 --> 00:08:37,703
<i>(Kemmel writes his name in the dust.)</i>

72
00:08:40,988 --> 00:08:43,285
JAMIE: Kemel? Well, I'm Jamie.
Kemel? 我叫 Jamie

73
00:08:43,333 --> 00:08:44,103
<i>(Kemel bows.)</i>

74
00:08:44,265 --> 00:08:51,107
JAMIE: He... hey, what is that?! Now come on now.
None of that. We're to be friends. Do you hear? Friends.
嘿。。嘿, 这什么意思？起来吧, 不要这样, 我们要做的是朋友, 你明白吗？朋友

75
00:08:55,872 --> 00:09:06,897
<i>(Kemel pulls a flower, wrapped in a paper from his belt.)</i>
<i>（Kemel 从他的腰带上拿出一朵花, 外面抱着一层纸）</i>
JAMIE: Aye. "V.W." I know, Victoria Waterfield.
啊, "V.W." 我知道, 代表 Victoria Waterfield

76
00:09:12,272 --> 00:09:18,297
<i>(Kemel points to the handkerchief. Then unwraps the flower.)</i>

77
00:09:21,379 --> 00:09:27,595
JAMIE: Oh, Miss Waterfield gave you the flower? You like her?
哦, Waterfield 小姐给了你这朵花？你喜欢她？

78
00:09:28,919 --> 00:09:32,218
JAMIE: Of course. Then what are we fighting for?
当然是了。那我们还打什么呀？

79
00:09:32,540 --> 00:09:39,120
JAMIE: Do you not know what I'm doing here, Kemel?
Victoria Waterfield is being held a prisoner here somewhere.
你知道我到这里来干什么的吧, Kemel? Victoria 被囚禁在这里的某个地方

80
00:09:39,372 --> 00:09:44,297
<i>(Kemel looks at Jamie, then up the the dark passage.)</i>

81
00:09:44,872 --> 00:09:49,497
<i>(He points to himeself, then Jamie and finally to the passage.)</i>

82
00:09:51,518 --> 00:09:57,658
JAMIE: Together? Aye, we'll go together. There's no one
I'd rather have with me.
一起？好, 我们一起去。现在我也不愿意其他人跟我在一起

83
00:10:00,172 --> 00:10:04,497
<i>(The Doctor is busy making calculations.)</i>

84
00:10:09,272 --> 00:10:14,497
<i>(They carry the body into the stables.)</i>

85
00:10:18,748 --> 00:10:21,565
WATERFIELD: What was that? Did you hear it?
那是什么？你听到了a吗？

86
00:10:21,825 --> 00:10:23,211
MAXTIBLE: Control your nerves.
别紧张

87
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:25,775
WATERFIELD: But there was a noise.
刚才的确有声音

88
00:10:27,283 --> 00:10:29,814
MAXTIBLE: Waterfield, go back to the house.
Waterfield, 回到房子里去

89
00:10:30,131 --> 00:10:34,593
WATERFIELD: Hmm? Oh, we have a task to perform.
唔, 我们还有任务得干呢

90
00:10:34,839 --> 00:10:38,082
MAXTIBLE: Waterfield, I am sick to death of you.
Waterfield, 我真是被你恶心死了

91
00:10:39,656 --> 00:10:40,529
WATERFIELD: What?
怎么了？

92
00:10:40,770 --> 00:10:44,113
MAXTIBLE: I take you into my house, you and your daughter - provide for you.
我把你们 - 你和你女儿 - 带到我的房子来, 还供你们吃住

93
00:10:44,334 --> 00:10:46,633
WATERFIELD: Yes, I know everything that you've done.
是的, 我知道你做的这一切

94
00:10:46,947 --> 00:10:54,437
MAXTIBLE: Small thanks do I get for it! I did not bring these terrible
creatures here deliberately, you know that. Am I to blame for everything?
但我得到了多少感谢？这些可怕的生物也不是我特意带来的, 你知道的, 这一切该怪我吗？

95
00:10:54,670 --> 00:10:56,169
WATERFIELD: No, no.
不, 不应该

96
00:10:56,427 --> 00:11:01,755
MAXTIBLE: No, it is your daughter they have kidnapped. One moment,
you beg me to do everything I can to rescue her; next moment, you blame me.
他们绑架的是你的女儿。这一会儿, 你求我做这做那以救她回来, 过一会儿, 你又怪我

97
00:11:01,949 --> 00:11:09,715
WATERFIELD: Yes. I... I don't mean it like that.
It's the price. First Kennedy, now this fellow.
是的。。。我并不是那个意思。这都是代价。先是 Kennedy, 现在又是这家伙

98
00:11:09,949 --> 00:11:14,715
WATERFIELD: How many people must die so that my daughter can live?
要死多少人才能救回我女儿?

99
00:11:15,266 --> 00:11:17,707
MAXTIBLE: We are not the murderers!
我们又不是凶手！

100
00:11:17,953 --> 00:11:25,388
WATERFIELD: No, just the silent partners. But we're equally to blame
because we stand by and do nothing.
不是，只是沉默的帮凶。但我们同样是有罪的，因为我们只是站在一边什么也不做

101
00:11:25,738 --> 00:11:33,543
MAXTIBLE: Go back to the house, Waterfield. I... I understand
you are under a stress. You... you try and get some sleep.
回你的房间去吧，Waterfield。我。。我明白你现在压力比较大。你。。你试试睡一觉吧

102
00:11:33,781 --> 00:11:38,216
WATERFIELD: Sleep? I've not had one good night's rest since this started.
睡觉？我一晚也没有睡好过，自打这事开始

103
00:11:38,697 --> 00:11:44,374
MAXTIBLE: There. You go back to your room. 
Near the end now. You've done enough.
去吧，回到你的房间去。快结束了。你已经做得够多了。

104
00:11:44,460 --> 00:11:49,220
<i>(Waterfield turns to leave. Maxtible takes out his gun.)</i>

105
00:11:49,524 --> 00:11:50,827
MAXTIBLE: What... what are you doing?
你。。你在干什么？

106
00:11:51,041 --> 00:11:52,163
TERRALL: Waterfield does not die yet!
Waterfield 现在还不能死

107
00:11:52,329 --> 00:11:54,061
MAXTIBLE: He says he will confess everything!
他说他会全部供出一切的

108
00:11:54,860 --> 00:11:59,220
<i>(Terrall takes the gun.)</i>

109
00:11:57,032 --> 00:12:04,536
TERRALL: Go back to the laboratory. I will dispose of the body. 
You will obey. You will obey!
回到实验室去。我会处理掉尸体的。你必须服从，你必须服从

110
00:12:09,260 --> 00:12:14,620
<i>(Jamie and Kemel watch a Dalek go by.)</i>

111
00:12:14,914 --> 00:12:19,945
JAMIE: Wait. Never mind about those, Kemel, 
unless they catch sight of us.
等等, 别管那些家伙, Kemel, 除非他们看到我们了。

112
00:12:20,114 --> 00:12:23,745
We seem to be going in the right direction.
看来我们走对方向了

113
00:12:23,860 --> 00:12:28,220
<i>(The Doctor continues to program the computer panel.)</i>

114
00:12:51,860 --> 00:12:56,220
<i>(Jamie knocks a button with his hand.)</i>

115
00:12:58,824 --> 00:12:59,572
JAMIE: Down!
趴下

116
00:13:01,860 --> 00:13:06,220
<i>(A heavy metal ball swings out from the light.)</i>

117
00:13:41,830 --> 00:13:48,317
DALEK: We do not trust you. What thoughts are you using now?
我们不相信你。你现在在想什么？

118
00:13:48,782 --> 00:13:55,491
DOCTOR: Human beings have five senses: sight, hearing, taste, smell and touch.
人类有五种感觉：视觉、听觉、味觉、嗅觉和触觉。

119
00:13:55,782 --> 00:14:02,491
DOCTOR: But there is instinct too. And Jamie used instinct to avoid your trap.
但还有一种叫做自觉。Jamie 就是用自觉避开了你们的陷阱

120
00:14:06,860 --> 00:14:11,220
<i>(Jamie and Kemel watch from the shadows.)</i>

121
00:14:30,660 --> 00:14:35,420
<i>(A light shines on the minstrels’ gallery door and the door opens.)</i>

122
00:14:37,866 --> 00:14:38,764
DALEK: Name?
名字?

123
00:14:39,576 --> 00:14:40,536
VICTORIA: Victoria.
维多利亚!

124
00:14:40,947 --> 00:14:42,455
DALEK: Louder.
大声点

125
00:14:43,441 --> 00:14:48,629
VICTORIA: Victoria! Victoria Waterfield! You know my name!
维多利亚! 维多利亚-瓦特菲尔德! 你们知道我的名字!

126
00:14:49,041 --> 00:14:57,441
DALEK: Silence. Inspection is over. Return to your room.
收声。检视结束了。回到你的房间去

127
00:15:00,160 --> 00:15:03,920
<i>(The door closes and the lights goes out.)</i>

128
00:15:04,165 --> 00:15:05,915
JAMIE: She's very beautiful, Kemel.
她很漂亮，Kemel

129
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:17,120
<i>(Kemel takes a mace from the wall.)</i>

130
00:15:20,016 --> 00:15:21,762
JAMIE: What are you going to do with that?
你打算拿着那个干什么用？

131
00:15:21,860 --> 00:15:26,120
<i>(Kemel points it towards the Dalek.)</i>

132
00:15:24,768 --> 00:15:31,810
JAMIE: You'll attack the Daleks - draw them off down the corridor,
你要攻击那些 Daleks, 把他们吸引到走廊里？

133
00:15:31,860 --> 00:15:36,120
<i>(Kemel nods, then points to the stairs.)</i>

134
00:15:34,168 --> 00:15:37,980
JAMIE: while I go up there and rescue her somehow?
好让我上那儿去, 把她救出来？

135
00:15:38,268 --> 00:15:44,980
JAMIE: It's too dangerous, Kemel. Besides, needs two of us up there. But how?
这太危险了, Kemel。另外, 需要两个人都进去才行。怎么办？

136
00:15:46,766 --> 00:15:51,392
DALEK: What is the significance of this thought pattern?
这个思维模式有什么用？

137
00:15:52,308 --> 00:15:56,568
DOCTOR: Suicidal attacks to gain an objective are stupid
为了赢得一个目标而进行自杀性袭击, 是愚蠢的

138
00:15:56,808 --> 00:16:01,568
DOCTOR: Self-preservation is a strong human factor.
自我保护是一种很强的人类特质

139
00:16:01,608 --> 00:16:05,568
DOCTOR: Jamie and his new friend are determined to succeed.
Jamie 和他的新朋友注定了会成功

140
00:16:05,608 --> 00:16:11,568
DOCTOR: But finding the girl is only part. Getting her away is another.
但找到这个女孩儿是一回事, 能把她救走又是另外一回事

141
00:16:17,574 --> 00:16:19,463
TERRALL: You'll come in here, Mollie, and explain yourself.
你给我进来, Mollie, 解释清楚

142
00:16:19,723 --> 00:16:22,231
MOLLIE: Oh... Oh, sir... Please, sir... You're hurting me!
噢。。噢, 先生。。求你了, 先生。。你弄疼我了

143
00:16:22,529 --> 00:16:25,158
TERRALL: Now, what is this hysterical nonsense?
说说, 到底是怎么一回事？

144
00:16:25,342 --> 00:16:28,075
MOLLIE: But sir, I heard Miss Victoria's voice!
但是, 先生, 我听到 Victoria 小姐的声音了

145
00:16:28,412 --> 00:16:31,507
TERRALL: Did she say how the weather was in Paris? That's where she is, Mollie.
那她说了巴黎的天气如何了吗？那是她现在呆的地方, Mollie

146
00:16:31,719 --> 00:16:34,298
MOLLIE: Well, I know that sir, but I heard her speaking.
是的, 我知道, 先生。但我的确听到她说话了

147
00:16:34,501 --> 00:16:35,224
TERRALL: Where?
在哪儿？

148
00:16:35,413 --> 00:16:40,726
MOLLIE: I was walking past the big fireplace in the hall sir,
and her voice sort of... floated out of it.
我从大厅的大壁炉前经过的时候, 先生, 她的声音就。。。飘了过来

149
00:16:40,930 --> 00:16:43,989
TERRALL: Will you explain how you could possibly hear
Miss Waterfield's voice when she's in Paris?!
那你解释一下既然 Waterfield 在巴黎, 你怎么能听到她的声音？

150
00:16:44,239 --> 00:16:47,514
MOLLIE: I know it can't be, sir, but I heard her, as plain as anything.
我知道这不可能, 先生, 但我听到她了, 的确是她的

151
00:16:47,791 --> 00:16:49,199
TERRALL: What were you doing in the hall?
那你那会儿在大厅里面干什么？

152
00:16:49,406 --> 00:16:50,592
MOLLIE: Oh, well. I wasn't doing anything wrong, sir.
哦, 这个, 我并没有干什么坏事, 先生

153
00:16:50,843 --> 00:16:52,023
TERRALL: What were you doing in this part of the house at this hour?!
你到底在这间房子里面做什么, 都这个时间了？

154
00:16:52,205 --> 00:16:52,864
MOLLIE: Oh, I don't know.
噢, 我不知道

155
00:16:53,064 --> 00:16:54,164
TERRALL: You do know, and you'll tell me!
你知道, 你得告诉我！

156
00:16:54,354 --> 00:16:55,626
RUTH: Arthur!

157
00:16:58,401 --> 00:17:00,619
TERRALL: I found this child creeping about the corridors.
我发现这个小丫头在走廊里鬼鬼祟祟的

158
00:17:00,799 --> 00:17:01,676
MOLLIE: I haven't done anything.
我什么也没干

159
00:17:01,866 --> 00:17:02,587
TERRALL: Be quiet!
收声！

160
00:17:03,065 --> 00:17:03,555
MOLLIE: Yes sir.
是, 先生

161
00:17:03,762 --> 00:17:05,738
TERRALL: She's miles from her room - should have been in bed an hour since!
她离她房间房间这么远 - 一个小时前就该上床睡觉了！

162
00:17:05,887 --> 00:17:07,280
RUTH: Did you have extra work this morning?
你早上是不是还有活儿要做？

163
00:17:07,519 --> 00:17:08,440
MOLLIE: Yes, Miss Ruth. I do.
是的, Ruth 小姐, 还有

164
00:17:08,612 --> 00:17:09,546
TERRALL: You're a liar!
你在撒谎！

165
00:17:10,008 --> 00:17:13,771
MOLLIE: Well, I haven't done anything, Miss. I haven't took nothing.
真的, 我什么也没做, 小姐。我什么也没拿

166
00:17:13,971 --> 00:17:17,124
RUTH: Arthur, the poor child's frightened out of her skin after this.
Arthur, 这可怜的小丫头都吓得不行了

167
00:17:17,299 --> 00:17:20,134
TERRALL: She's nothing but play acting. She's a mean, sniveling little minx.
她这都是在假扮无辜呢, 她是个带着假面的恶毒小妖精

168
00:17:20,484 --> 00:17:21,570
MOLLIE: But I haven't done anything. I haven't.
但我什么也没有做过, 没有

169
00:17:21,759 --> 00:17:24,673
TERRALL: Go to the sitting room and wait there.
Mr. Maxtible will decide what to do with you.
到客厅去等着, Maxtible 先生会决定对你如何处置

170
00:17:24,930 --> 00:17:25,447
MOLLIE: But sir, I...
但是先生, 我。。。

171
00:17:25,676 --> 00:17:26,754
TERRALL: Do as you are told!
照我说的做！

172
00:17:28,218 --> 00:17:32,351
RUTH: Come on, it's all right. Everything will be all right.
来吧, 没事的, 一切都会弄明白的

173
00:17:36,571 --> 00:17:39,352
RUTH: Arthur, tell me what's wrong.
Authur, 告诉我哪里不对劲？

174
00:17:40,102 --> 00:17:41,813
TERRALL: Wrong? Why should something be wrong?
不对劲？为什么得有什么事不对劲？

175
00:17:43,075 --> 00:17:45,892
RUTH: Has my father influenced you in some way?
我父亲跟你说了什么吗？

176
00:17:47,584 --> 00:17:49,511
TERRALL: No, not your father.
不, 不是你父亲

177
00:17:50,644 --> 00:17:56,362
RUTH: Come away with me please! I somehow feel if we delay, it will be too late.
请跟我来吧。不知怎么的, 我感觉如果我们再拖的话, 就太迟了

178
00:17:58,441 --> 00:18:02,840
TERRALL: I can't go. Not yet.
我不能去, 还不到时候

179
00:18:04,039 --> 00:18:07,627
MAXTIBLE: I have done everything you have asked me to. 
你们让我做的所有事情, 我都做了

180
00:18:08,039 --> 00:18:15,627
MAXTIBLE: You wanted an agency here on Earth to plan and prepare things for you. I have been that agency.
你们想要在地球上有一个代理机构，帮你们做些谋划和准备, 我就成了这个代理

181
00:18:16,039 --> 00:18:21,627
MAXTIBLE: Will you please tell those who give you orders that
I am getting tired of waiting.
你能不能转告那些下命令的, 说我已经厌倦了等待了

182
00:18:21,935 --> 00:18:24,612
DALEK: Do you threaten the Daleks?
你是在威胁 Daleks 吗?

183
00:18:24,870 --> 00:18:29,925
MAXTIBLE: Oh, surely threatening is not necessary. We have a...
a partnership - an understanding.
噢, 当然了并不是威胁。我们。。。是有伙伴关系, 有共识的

184
00:18:30,248 --> 00:18:32,532
DALEK: You have obeyed us.
你一直很听话

185
00:18:32,838 --> 00:18:35,392
MAXTIBLE: You have a strange way of putting things.
你们的表达方式很奇怪

186
00:18:35,438 --> 00:18:40,192
MAXTIBLE: I prefer to say that you have asked for certain services.
我倒愿意用这样的说法：你们请求我们提供某些服务

187
00:18:40,338 --> 00:18:45,792
MAXTIBLE: I have, uh... provided those services punctually and efficiently.
我也一直很高效很准确地提供了这些服务

188
00:18:45,838 --> 00:18:48,792
MAXTIBLE: Now you really must look to your side of the bargain.
但你们现在真的必须看一下你们这边了

189
00:18:48,838 --> 00:18:51,792
MAXTIBLE: It is not beyond me to ruin the entire enterprise.
我还真是不能理解, 你们会毁了这笔交易

190
00:18:52,211 --> 00:18:54,321
MAXTIBLE: Oh, oh, oh, ho!
噢, 噢, 噢, 噢！

191
00:18:54,516 --> 00:18:57,705
DALEK: Do not threaten! Obey!
不要威胁我们! 要服从！

192
00:18:57,947 --> 00:19:00,738
MAXTIBLE: Yes, very well! I understand!
好, 好的！我懂了！

193
00:19:02,380 --> 00:19:04,953
DALEK: Obey the Daleks.
服从 Daleks

194
00:19:05,469 --> 00:19:09,076
MAXTIBLE: No. Please... Please wait!
不, 求你了, 等等！

195
00:19:11,061 --> 00:19:18,184
MAXTIBLE: The secret... the secret. You promised to give it to me!
That is why I have done all this!
秘密, 那个秘密。你们承诺了给我的！所以我才做这一切的啊！

196
00:19:18,423 --> 00:19:25,235
DALEK: The Daleks know many secrets. You will learn the most important.
Daleks 知道很多秘密, 你将会得到最重要的

197
00:19:27,121 --> 00:19:33,311
(The Dalek returns to the cabinet.)

198
00:19:34,755 --> 00:19:38,251
MAXTIBLE: I must not be frightened of them.
我不能被他们吓倒

199
00:19:38,355 --> 00:19:43,351
MAXTIBLE: It's just their way. Th... They're different people - alien.
这是他们的方式。。他们跟我们不同, 是外星人

200
00:19:43,455 --> 00:19:47,751
MAXTIBLE: But they will tell me! Of course they will!
但他们会告诉我的, 当然会！

201
00:19:48,644 --> 00:19:49,697
RUTH: Father!
父亲

202
00:19:50,038 --> 00:19:51,926
MAXTIBLE: Ruth, I told you not to come in here - under any circumstances.
Ruth, 我告诉过你不要到这里来, 不管任何情况下

203
00:19:52,251 --> 00:19:57,402
RUTH: Father, I simply had to.
I heard you speaking to someone and there's no one here.
父亲, 我只是不得不来。我听到你在跟谁说话, 但这里没有人

204
00:19:57,551 --> 00:20:00,402
And Arthur is involved in some way.
而且 Arthur 不知怎么也卷进来了

205
00:20:00,796 --> 00:20:02,626
MAXTIBLE: Oh, Arthur. Yes.
哦, Arthur, 是的

206
00:20:02,870 --> 00:20:09,363
RUTH: Why has he become so changed? 
And Victoria Waterfield - where is she?
为什么他变化这么大？ 还有 Victoria Waterfield, 她在哪儿？

207
00:20:10,556 --> 00:20:14,805
MAXTIBLE: My child, these are questions that I cannot answer.
我的孩子, 这些问题我都回答不了

208
00:20:14,856 --> 00:20:22,345
MAXTIBLE: But, my dear, I will tell you one thing - one thing only,
不过, 亲爱的, 我可以告诉你一件事 - 就这一件

209
00:20:22,556 --> 00:20:28,945
MAXTIBLE: and then perhaps you may understand why there are secrets to be kept.
然后你也许就会明白, 为什么会有这些秘密

210
00:20:31,829 --> 00:20:32,926
MAXTIBLE: You see this?
你看见这个了吗？

211
00:20:33,197 --> 00:20:33,923
RUTH: What is it?
这是什么?

212
00:20:34,184 --> 00:20:37,953
MAXTIBLE: A piece of ordinary metal of very little value, would you not say so?
一小块普通的金属, 它不值钱, 你不觉得吗？

213
00:20:38,169 --> 00:20:39,087
RUTH: I suppose so.
我也这么想

214
00:20:39,347 --> 00:20:43,463
MAXTIBLE: What does it weigh? A few pounds? Five, six, shall we say?
它有多重？好几磅？ 5磅, 6磅, 我们估计

215
00:20:43,547 --> 00:20:49,863
MAXTIBLE: For centuries now, men have searched for the greatest secret of all.
几个世纪以来, 人类都在探索这项终极秘密

216
00:20:50,047 --> 00:20:53,263
MAXTIBLE: Some say it was known to the ancient alchemists.
有的人说, 古代的炼金术士知道这个

217
00:20:53,347 --> 00:20:56,263
MAXTIBLE: Some say that the secret never existed at all.
有的人说, 这项秘密从来不存在

218
00:20:56,347 --> 00:21:00,263
MAXTIBLE: But still, the stories and the rumours, and the search goes on!
尽管如此, 故事、流言, 以及探索, 都从未停止

219
00:21:00,524 --> 00:21:01,741
RUTH: What secret?!
什么秘密

220
00:21:02,028 --> 00:21:06,469
MAXTIBLE: The transmutation of metal into gold. Changing metal into gold.
金属到金子的转化方法, 把金属变成金子

221
00:21:07,028 --> 00:21:13,469
MAXTIBLE: Now, perhaps, do you begin to understand a little?
现在, 你是不是开始有点明白了？

222
00:21:14,028 --> 00:21:19,469
MAXTIBLE: To possess such a secret would mean power and influence beyond all imagination.
拥有这样一向秘密就意味着有了不可想象的力量和权利

223
00:21:20,028 --> 00:21:26,469
MAXTIBLE: And I am about to discover this secret. Nothing will stop me. Nothing! Nobody!
而我正要发现这个秘密了。没有什么可以挡住我, 没有谁！

224
00:21:35,194 --> 00:21:36,124
DALEK: Name?
名字?

225
00:21:36,938 --> 00:21:37,994
VICTORIA: Victoria.
维多利亚

226
00:21:38,447 --> 00:21:39,670
DALEK: Louder!
大声点

227
00:21:40,078 --> 00:21:42,123
VICTORIA: Victoria Waterfield!
维多利亚-瓦特菲尔德!

228
00:21:42,424 --> 00:21:43,830
VICTORIA: Victoria Waterfield!
维多利亚-瓦特菲尔德!

229
00:21:45,196 --> 00:21:51,207
DALEK: Inspection is over. Return to your room.
检视结束了, 回到你的房间去吧

230
00:21:53,623 --> 00:21:58,235
<i>(Victoria goes back to her room and the lights goes out.)</i> 

231
00:22:06,910 --> 00:22:11,504
<i>(Jamie gives Kemel one end of the rope, and circles around the Dalek.)</i>

232
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:17,000
(Together they pull the rope, sending the Dalek crashing into the fireplace.)

233
00:22:20,710 --> 00:22:21,904
JAMIE: Well, that's fixed that one.

234
00:22:26,910 --> 00:22:31,504
<i>(They run to beneath the gallery.)</i>

235
00:22:37,910 --> 00:22:42,504
<i>(Kemel throws the rope over the banister and pulls it tight.)</i>

236
00:22:48,910 --> 00:22:53,504
<i>(Jamie climbs the rope.)</i>

237
00:23:10,110 --> 00:23:15,704
<i>(He reaches the top and climbs onto the landing.)</i>

238
00:23:15,910 --> 00:23:20,504
<i>(Kemel starts climbing up.)</i>

239
00:23:29,176 --> 00:23:30,731
Look out, the rail's going to break!

240
00:23:32,910 --> 00:23:37,504
<i>(He continues climbing.)</i>

241
00:23:56,910 --> 00:24:01,504
<i>(Jamie helps Kemel onto the landing.)</i>

242
00:24:08,334 --> 00:24:13,263
JAMIE: Miss Waterfield? Can you open the door? We've come to get you.
Waterfield 小姐, 你能把门打开吗？我们来救你了

243
00:24:13,410 --> 00:24:18,104
<i>(Unnoticed, a Dalek comes out of the shadows.)</i>

